title: ASUS X00GD with 5.2-inch display and 4,850mAh battery gets certified by TENAA
text:
ASUS X00GD with 5.2-inch display and 4,850mAh battery gets certified by TENAA ASUS X00GD with 5.2-inch display and 4,850mAh battery gets certified by TENAA By January 2, 2017 “The ASUS XOOGD sports up to 4GB RAM, a 13MP camera and Android Nougat” 
A new ASUS smartphone dubbed the X00GD has surfaced on Chinese certification website TENAA . The main highlight of the smartphone is the massive 4,850mAh battery which it manages to pack into a fairly compact form factor. According to the listing, the ASUS X00GD sports a 5.2-inch display and is powered by an octa-core processor clocked at 1.5GHz. The device will ship with a fingerprint sensor inside the home button and will come in three different models sporting 2GB /3GB /4GB of RAM paired with 16GB/ 32GB/ 64GB of storage respectively. In the camera department, the smartphone gets a pair of 13MP and 8MP sensors on the back and the front respectively. Weighing 169.5g and measuring 149.5 × 73.7 × 8.85mm, the X00GD runs Android Nougat upon first boot. The smartphone will come in hues of luxury gold, rose gold, and black. ASUS hasn’t made any official announcements yet.
